Label: Hunza_hunz1248
Name: Hunza
Comment: The main source used to collect this language used Burusho terms. Burusho is a sub-group of Hunza.

Label: Ottowa_Ojibwa_otta1242
Name: Ottowa Ojibwa
Comment: Could be ottowa ojibwa, or central ojibwa. The source is unclear. Ottowa's geographic location in Glottolog is closer to the description in the original source

Label: Ngaatjatjarra_ngaa1240
Name: Ngaatjatjarra
Comment: Ngaatjatjara could be the same as Ngaanyatjarra, in which case the language has been collected twice.

Label: Kung_juho1239
Name: !Kung, Southeastern Ju, or Ju'hoan
Comment: This language has many different names. Kung was chosen for the project file due to lack of special characters, even if ju'hoansi is the one now viewed to be correct.
